---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about Nachiket Kulkarni — Principal Platform Engineer with close to 10 years of experience, currently at Autodesk, Georgia Tech MS CS alumnus."
>
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="section-label">About Me</p>
    <h1 class="section-title">Background & Story</h1>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-content">
        <p>
          I'm <strong>Nachiket Kulkarni</strong>, a <strong>Principal Platform Engineer</strong> with close to
          10 years of experience designing and operating large-scale cloud infrastructure, internal developer
          platforms, CI/CD systems, and data infrastructure. I currently work at <strong>Autodesk</strong>
          in Pune, India, where I help drive platform engineering initiatives for enterprise clients including
          Pixar, Hyundai, and L&amp;T.
        </p>
        <p>
          My journey started in QA and test automation at TIBCO Software, where I built a strong foundation
          in software reliability, observability, and engineering discipline. Over the years I transitioned
          into DevOps and platform engineering — building pipelines, managing Kubernetes clusters, designing
          infrastructure as code, and enabling developer self-service at NICE, Coupa Software, and Autodesk.
        </p>
        <p>
          I hold a <strong>Master of Science in Computer Science</strong> from the
          <strong>Georgia Institute of Technology</strong> (Georgia Tech), which strengthened my foundations
          in distributed systems, machine learning, and systems design. Today, my work increasingly sits at
          the intersection of platform engineering and AI/ML, where I focus on scalable MLOps platforms,
          model delivery workflows, and cloud-native systems that support modern engineering teams.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm passionate about building golden paths for developers — creating secure, observable,
          and cost-efficient platforms that improve engineering velocity without sacrificing reliability.
          Outside of work, I enjoy contributing to open-source projects, exploring LLM tooling,
          and building practical automation in Python.
        </p>

        <div class="skills-section">
          <h2 class="skills-heading">Core Skills</h2>
          <div class="skills-grid">
            <div class="skill-group">
              <h3>Platform & Cloud</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Platform Engineering</li>
                <li>AWS (EKS, ECS, RDS, S3, IAM)</li>
                <li>GCP (GKE, BigQuery, Cloud Run)</li>
                <li>Terraform / OpenTofu</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="skill-group">
              <h3>Kubernetes & Delivery</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Kubernetes & Helm</li>
                <li>GitHub Actions</li>
                <li>Jenkins</li>
                <li>ArgoCD / FluxCD</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="skill-group">
              <h3>Observability & Reliability</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Prometheus & Grafana</li>
                <li>ELK / OpenSearch Stack</li>
                <li>Datadog</li>
                <li>OpenTelemetry</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="skill-group">
              <h3>Languages & MLOps</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>Python (primary)</li>
                <li>Bash / Shell scripting</li>
                <li>FastAPI / Streamlit</li>
                <li>MLflow / KServe</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="about-sidebar">
        <div class="info-card">
          <h2 class="info-card-title">Quick Info</h2>
          <dl class="info-list">
            <div class="info-item">
              <dt>📍 Location</dt>
              <dd>Pune, India</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="info-item">
              <dt>🏢 Company</dt>
              <dd>Autodesk</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="info-item">
              <dt>🎓 Education</dt>
              <dd>MS CS, Georgia Tech</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="info-item">
              <dt>💼 Experience</dt>
              <dd>Close to 10 years</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="info-item">
              <dt>🌐 Focus</dt>
              <dd>Platform Engineering, Cloud, MLOps</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <div class="info-links">
            <a href="https://github.com/nachikul" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="info-link">
              GitHub →
            </a>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nkulkarni9493" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="info-link">
              LinkedIn →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-content p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 70ch;
  }
  .about-content p strong { color: var(--text-heading); }

  .skills-section { margin-top: 2.5rem; }

  .skills-heading {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  .skills-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .skill-group {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .skill-group h3 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .skill-group ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .skill-group li {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .skill-group li::before {
    content: '›';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Sidebar */
  .info-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.75rem;
    position: sticky;
    top: 80px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .info-card-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  .info-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .info-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.15rem;
  }

  .info-item dt {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .info-item dd {
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .info-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .info-link {
    display: block;
    padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .info-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    color: var(--accent);
    background: var(--accent-dim);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .info-card { position: static; }
    .skills-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 500px) {
    .skills-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
